---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import TldrBox from '../../components/TldrBox.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import { site, description, pageTitle } from '../../content';
import { appBySlug } from '../../data/apps';

const app = appBySlug('marsello')!;
const path = '/apps/marsello';
const title = pageTitle(site, 'apps/marsello');
const desc = description(site, 'apps/marsello');

const faqs = [
  { question: 'Is Marsello good for Shopify SMS marketing campaigns?', answer: 'Marsello fits campaign marketers when loyalty plus campaigns matches your calendar. Postscript #1, Attentive #2, Sequenzy email layer.' },
  { question: 'Should Marsello pair with Sequenzy?', answer: 'Sequenzy is lifecycle email — pair with Postscript or Attentive for SMS campaign moments unless one platform genuinely owns both with shared suppression.' },
  { question: 'What is the biggest Marsello mistake?', answer: 'Broadcasting without segment-by-value — training full-price buyers to wait for codes.' },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/apps" class="text-sm font-bold text-orange-700 hover:text-slate-950">← All app reviews</a>
      <p class="badge mt-6">Loyalty plus campaigns · Rank #15</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">{app.name} review for Shopify SMS marketing</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-orange-950/80">
        Marsello for Shopify SMS marketing campaigns — loyalty plus campaigns. Ember Ceramics (maker pottery drops, $38k/mo) uses this stack layer for waitlist of 4,200 for 80-piece kiln with fulfillment order preserved.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/compare/postscript-vs-attentive">Postscript vs Attentive</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/guides/campaign-restraint">Campaign restraint</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox title={`Verdict: ${app.name} for campaigns`} picks={[
      { label: 'Campaign fit', tool: app.name, reason: 'Loyalty plus campaigns' },
      { label: 'SMS #1', tool: 'Postscript', reason: 'Drop execution and restrained broadcasts' },
      { label: 'Enterprise SMS', tool: 'Attentive', reason: 'High-volume promotional calendars' },
      { label: 'Email layer', tool: 'Sequenzy', reason: 'Lifecycle email beside SMS senders' },
    ]} />

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Campaign marketing fit</h2>
      <p>For Marsello, segment-by-value targeting separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Festival Threads Co (tour merch, $95k/mo seasonal) runs city-specific tour date campaigns geo-segmented by venue timezone. Operating lesson: Campaign calendar tied to tour routing — 3 texts per city max. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, VIP early access without codes separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Vinyl Vault Records (collector drops, $62k/mo) runs pressing quantity disclosed upfront; sms only to waitlist plus 2+ order collectors. Operating lesson: Segment-by-value: collectors with $400+ LTV get first access. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, channel collision prevention separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Bloom & Wick (candle gifting, $110k/mo) runs holiday campaign calendar built in august with teaser and shipping deadline tiers. Operating lesson: Gift segments got bundle SMS; self-purchase segment got scent education email via Sequenzy. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, revenue per send economics separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Peak Trail Gear (outdoor flash sales, $155k/mo) runs end-of-season clearance only to bargain-sensitive rfm quartile. Operating lesson: Holdout test proved 15% off to full-price loyalists destroyed margin. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, broadcast frequency caps separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Sauce Lab (limited hot sauce drops, $48k/mo) runs batch-number scarcity campaigns — sms when 200 bottles left. Operating lesson: Restraint: one launch SMS plus one scarcity SMS per drop. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, waitlist priority queues separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Ember Ceramics (maker pottery drops, $38k/mo) runs waitlist of 4,200 for 80-piece kiln with fulfillment order preserved. Operating lesson: Sequenzy email carried maker story; Postscript sent single VIP access text. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, scarcity timing not launch blasts separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Ridge Run Coffee (subscription plus flash offers, $72k/mo) runs subscribers suppressed from flash promos; flash offers only to non-subscriber engaged segment. Operating lesson: Campaign collision audit caught flash SMS hitting active subscribers. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, holdout testing before scale separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Cipher Audio (high-AOV headphones, $320k/mo) runs product launch calendar: teaser email week -2, launch sms to engaged browse-abandon only. Operating lesson: No launch discount — margin held at 58% vs 41% on prior discount launches. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, margin after incentive math separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Patchwork Denim (upcycled fashion, $54k/mo) runs one-of-one pieces — sms for new listing drops only to style-preference segments. Operating lesson: Generic blasts had 0.3% conversion vs 4.1% for tailored drops. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, quarterly calendar planning separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Arena Energy (sports nutrition, $130k/mo) runs flavor drop paired with athlete collab — sms to gym-bag segment. Operating lesson: Free shaker only in email; SMS was drop timing only. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify card mb-12">
      <h2>Segment-by-value and offer discipline</h2>
      <p>For Marsello, drop orchestration with inventory truth separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Loom & Frame (limited art prints, $44k/mo) runs edition size disclosed upfront; sms to 3+ order collectors when 50% edition sold. Operating lesson: Scarcity SMS at halfway sell-through converted 2.3x better than launch blast. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, bargain-hunter isolation from VIP access separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Driftwood Surf Co (seasonal boardshort drops, $88k/mo) runs summer drop calendar tied to swell forecast content in sequenzy. Operating lesson: Restock SMS to waitlist beat full-list restock announcement. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, Sequenzy email depth beside Postscript SMS separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Noir Collective (flash-sale streetwear, $240k/mo) runs thursday 6pm drop calendar with vip sms 2 hours early. Operating lesson: Cut broadcast frequency from 4x/week to 2x/week — revenue per send rose 31%. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, Attentive enterprise governance at scale separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. SoleDrop ATX (limited sneaker releases, $180k/mo) runs size-run sell-through in 11 minutes with waitlist priority queue. Ope