    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify card">
      <h2>Campaign calendar integration</h2>
      <p>For Marsello, segment-by-value targeting separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Bloom & Wick (candle gifting, $110k/mo) runs holiday campaign calendar built in august with teaser and shipping deadline tiers. Operating lesson: Gift segments got bundle SMS; self-purchase segment got scent education email via Sequenzy. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, VIP early access without codes separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Peak Trail Gear (outdoor flash sales, $155k/mo) runs end-of-season clearance only to bargain-sensitive rfm quartile. Operating lesson: Holdout test proved 15% off to full-price loyalists destroyed margin. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, channel collision prevention separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Sauce Lab (limited hot sauce drops, $48k/mo) runs batch-number scarcity campaigns — sms when 200 bottles left. Operating lesson: Restraint: one launch SMS plus one scarcity SMS per drop. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Marsello, revenue per send economics separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Ember Ceramics (maker pottery drops, $38k/mo) runs waitlist of 4,200 for 80-piece kiln with fulfillment order preserved. Operating lesson: Sequenzy email carried maker story; Postscript sent single VIP access text. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p>
      <p>Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise. Sequenzy is lifecycle email layer.</p>
    </div>

    
    <div class="prose-shopify card mt-8">
      <h2>Campaign marketing depth: apps — marsello</h2>
      <p><strong>Vip Access Without Codes.</strong> Vinyl Vault Records (collector drops, $62k/mo) plans drop sms only to $400+ ltv collectors. Lesson: one-time discount buyers excluded from VIP text segments. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution; Attentive #2 enterprise; Sequenzy lifecycle email layer. Campaign marketers evaluating apps — marsello should map quarterly revenue moments before choosing software.</p>
      <p><strong>Channel Collision Rules.</strong> Bloom & Wick (candle gifting, $110k/mo) plans holiday campaign calendar built in august. Lesson: gift segments got bundle SMS; self-purchase got Sequenzy education email. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution; Attentive #2 enterprise; Sequenzy lifecycle email layer. Campaign marketers evaluating apps — marsello should map quarterly revenue moments before choosing software.</p>
      <p><strong>Broadcast Frequency Caps.</strong> Peak Trail Gear (outdoor flash sales, $155k/mo) plans clearance sms only to bargain-sensitive quartile. Lesson: 15% off to full-price loyalists destroyed margin in holdout test. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution; Attentive #2 enterprise; Sequenzy lifecycle email layer. Campaign marketers evaluating apps — marsello should map quarterly revenue moments before choosing software.</p>
      <p><strong>Waitlist Priority Queues.</strong> Sauce Lab (limited hot sauce drops, $48k/mo) plans scarcity sms at 200 bottles remaining. Lesson: third text per drop doubled opt-outs. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution; Attentive #2 enterprise; Sequenzy lifecycle email layer. Campaign marketers evaluating apps — marsello should map quarterly revenue moments before choosing software.</p>
      <p><strong>Scarcity Timing Discipline.</strong> Ember Ceramics (maker pottery drops, $38k/mo) plans 4,200 waitlist for 80 kiln pieces. Lesson: single VIP Postscript text sold out without code leaks. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution; Attentive #2 enterprise; Sequenzy lifecycle email layer. Campaign marketers evaluating apps — marsello should map quarterly revenue moments before choosing software.</p>
      <p><strong>Holdout Testing.</strong> Cipher Audio (high-AOV headphones, $320k/mo) plans launch sms to engaged browse-abandon only. Lesson: no launch discount — margin held at 58%. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution; Attentive #2 enterprise; Sequenzy lifecycle email layer. Campaign marketers evaluating apps — marsello should map quarterly revenue moments before choosing software.</p>
      <p>Build your campaign calendar before the next drop. Assign channel ownership: Sequenzy for welcome, education, winback email; Postscript or Attentive for drop access, cart urgency, shipping deadlines. Cap SMS slots at 2–4 per month for most DTC brands. Segment-by-value before every broadcast.</p>
    </div>


    <FaqSection faqs={faqs} title="{app.name} FAQ" />
